INSERT INTO public.messages VALUES ('1852466e-4cf9-4ebc-bab4-3316903d045d', '983b3453-363e-449c-bae8-d33ab7f6296b', '<p>Alright, I''d love to help with that! Market intelligence and competitive research are key for understanding your industry, customers, and competition. Here''s a few steps you might take:</p>
<h3>1. Identify your competition:</h3>
<p>Start by making a list of your main competitors. Think about both direct competitors (those who offer a very similar product or service) and indirect competitors (those who offer a different product or service that could also meet your customers'' needs).</p>
<h3>2. Research your competition:</h3>
<p>Next, delve into each competitor''s product, pricing, marketing strategy, and customer reviews. This can give you a sense of their strengths and weaknesses.</p>
<h3>3. Understand your customers:</h3>
<p>Use surveys, interviews, and other research methods to understand who your customers are, what they need, and why they choose your product over others.</p>
<h3>4. Analyze market trends:</h3>
<p>Look at industry reports, news articles, and other sources to understand the trends that are shaping your market.</p>
