INSERT INTO public.messages VALUES ('a94511c9-ac7c-4749-9f4c-1bc604717591', '402e984c-d479-48ab-97fd-8b566a27959e', '<p>Alright, when it comes to calculating processing rates, there are usually three main types to consider:</p>
<h3>1. Flat-Rate Pricing</h3>
<p>This is the simplest form where you''re charged a fixed percentage per transaction. For instance, if the rate is 2.75%, and you process a $100 sale, you''ll pay $2.75 in fees.</p>
<h3>2. Tiered Pricing</h3>
<p>Here, transactions fall into one of several tiers (qualified, mid-qualified, or non-qualified) based on factors like transaction method and card type. Each tier has a different rate.</p>
<h3>3. Interchange-Plus Pricing</h3>
<p>This pricing model includes two parts: the interchange fee (set by credit card networks and paid to the card-issuing bank) and the processor''s markup. It''s more transparent but can be more complex to calculate.</p>
<p>For more detailed calculations and examples, you''d need to know the specific rates and tiers a processor is offering. If you want to dive deeper into this topic, I''ve found some relevant documents:</p>
