INSERT INTO public.training_interactions VALUES ('60379fa8-70a2-4257-9db8-3f74da3409ac', 'Test: What are typical merchant processing fees?', '<p>Typical merchant processing fees can include:</p>

<h2>Key Points:</h2>
<ul>
<li>Interchange fees - Fees paid to the card-issuing bank, typically 1-2% of the transaction amount</li>
<li>Assessment fees - Fees paid to the card networks (Visa, Mastercard, etc.), usually 0.10-0.15% of the transaction</li>
<li>Processor markup - The fee charged by the merchant services provider, typically 0.20-0.50% of the transaction</li>
</ul>

<p>The total merchant processing fees can range from around 1.5% to 3% of the transaction amount, depending on the specific rates negotiated with the merchant services provider. Additional fees may apply for things like monthly statements, PCI compliance, and other services.</p>

