INSERT INTO public.training_interactions VALUES ('32deed75-d2cd-4476-af9e-745319851c2f', 'How do I calculate interchange rates for a restaurant?', '<p>To calculate interchange rates for a restaurant merchant, you''ll need to consider the types of transactions they process and the associated interchange fees.</p>

<br>

<h2>Key Points:</h2>
<ul>
<li>Restaurants typically process a mix of card-present (swiped/inserted) and card-not-present (online/phone) transactions.</li>
<li>Card-present transactions have lower interchange rates, while card-not-present transactions have higher rates.</li>
<li>Other factors that impact interchange include the card type (e.g. consumer vs. commercial), whether tips are included, and the transaction amount.</li>
</ul>

<br>

<p>To get an accurate estimate, you''ll need to gather details on the restaurant''s transaction mix, average ticket size, and any other relevant data. This will allow you to calculate a blended interchange rate that accounts for the unique processing profile of the business.</p>

