INSERT INTO public.training_interactions VALUES ('d13220a2-4997-4978-99c0-9898e54fea14', 'what happens on a charge back with shift4', '<p>When a chargeback occurs with Shift4, the merchant will be notified and the funds from the disputed transaction will be temporarily held or "frozen" in the merchant''s account.</p>

<br>

<h2>Key Points:</h2>
<ul>
<li>Shift4 will investigate the chargeback claim and request documentation from the merchant to defend the transaction.</li>
<li>The merchant has a limited time frame (usually 10-14 days) to provide a response and supporting evidence to Shift4.</li>
<li>If the merchant is able to successfully dispute the chargeback, the funds will be released back to the merchant''s account. If not, the funds will be deducted.</li>
</ul>

<br>

<p>It''s important for merchants to have clear policies and procedures in place to handle chargebacks efficiently with Shift4. Providing timely and thorough documentation is key to resolving chargebacks in the merchant''s favor.</p>

