INSERT INTO public.training_interactions VALUES ('0ecc14e0-95c4-40d4-9919-71911339019c', 'What are the different pricing models for Square?', 'Here''s a breakdown of the different pricing models offered by Square:

<p>According to the information in our knowledge base, Square offers the following pricing models for merchant services:</p>

<div style="background: white; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px; border-left: 4px solid #10b981;">
<h3 style="color: #1e293b; margin: 0 0 8px 0; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600;">Flat-Rate Pricing</h3>
<p style="color: #475569; margin: 0; font-size: 14px;">Square''s standard pricing model charges a flat rate of 2.6% + $0.10 per in-person transaction, and 2.9% + $0.30 per online/mobile transaction. This simple, transparent pricing is easy for merchants to understand.</p>
</div>

<br>

<div style="background: white; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px; border-left: 4px solid #f59e0b;">
<h3 style="color: #1e293b; margin: 0 0 8px 0; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600;">Interchange-Plus Pricing</h3>
<p style="color: #475569; margin: 0; font-size: 14px;">Square also offers an interchange-plus pricing model, which charges the actual interchange fees set by the card networks, plus an additional percentage and per-transaction fee. This model can provide more cost savings for high-volume merchants.</p>
</div>

<br>

<div style="background: white; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px; border-left: 4px solid #8b5cf6;">
<h3 style="color: #1e293b; margin: 0 0 8px 0; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600;">Customized Pricing</h3>
<p style="color: #475569; margin: 0; font-size: 14px;">For larger enterprises, Square offers custom pricing packages that can be tailored to the merchant''s specific needs and transaction volume. This allows for more flexibility and potential cost savings.</p>
</div>

