INSERT INTO public.training_interactions VALUES ('4d7619a0-b65d-41a5-8855-6f037a89a774', 'what is the pci info for trx', '<p>The PCI (Payment Card Industry) information for TRX (Transaction) typically refers to the standards and requirements for securely handling and processing payment card data during transactions.</p>

<p>For TRX specifically, PCI compliance involves:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Secure data transmission:</strong> Ensuring cardholder data is encrypted during the transaction process.</li>
  <li><strong>Data storage:</strong> Avoiding storage of sensitive authentication data post-authorization.</li>
  <li><strong>Access controls:</strong> Restricting access to cardholder data to authorized personnel only.</li>
  <li><strong>Regular security testing:</strong> Conducting vulnerability scans and penetration testing.</li>
  <li><strong>Maintaining PCI DSS compliance:</strong> Following the PCI Data Security Standard (PCI DSS) requirements applicable to the merchant''s environment.</li>
</ul>

